    en: "Narcan, the brand name for naloxone, is a medicine that reverses an opioid overdose. NY Public Health Law § 3309 created the Opioid Overdose Prevention Program (OOPP) and allows any trained layperson — family members, friends, or anyone in a position to help — to legally carry and administer naloxone. A statewide pharmacy standing order lets any NY pharmacy dispense naloxone without an individual prescription. Free kits are available in Monroe County from the Department of Health, Trillium Health, and Hope Dealers BTC. Good-faith administration carries civil and criminal immunity under PBH § 3309 and § 3000-a."
